This paper deals with designing mechanisms for optimizing revenue in auctions, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the behavior of buyers, which involves learning and decision-making, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The mechanism design involves state-based algorithms, which can be categorized under data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with revenue optimization, which is a key aspect of economics (cs.EC).
